	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64277876"><p><div class="quote"><p>cut the old tnt off the outside of the core</p></div><p>It is not TNT. It is paraffin-stabilized RDX, also known as hexogen.</p><p>RDX is more powerful than TNT but also more stable. You can literally set it on fire, and it will explode.</p><p>RDX is the explosive in C-4 plastique and Semtex.</p><p>Torpex, a blend of RDX, TNT, and powdered aluminum, was used for carpet bombing in WW2.</p><p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RDX" title="wikipedia.org">RDX</a> [wikipedia.org]</p></div>
	</div>

